snippet.textDisplay:
This reaction is not safe and you shouldn't stand your ground. First, it is extremely exothermic and the foam would give you thermal burns. Second, there is a lot of unreacted hydrogen peroxide, which can cause chemical burns. Third, much of the iodide ion got oxidized into elemental iodine, resulting in the brown/yellow seen. You don't want to get this on the skin or eyes- this will stain skin and cause chemical damage. It is not eco-friendly due to the same reasons above.

Having an uncontrolled reaction like this is extremely reckless. What if the floating cloud landed on someone and burned them or someone got trapped under the burning hot foam?
